Parliament, Saturday, 04 August 2018 – The Chairperson of the Portfolio Committee on Police, Mr Francois Beukman, will today evening conduct an unannounced visit to the Macassar Police Station, City of Cape Town, Western Cape. The visit will start at 19:00. The visit is a response to representations made by various groups, including the Macassar Safety Forum, to Mr Beukman to visit the Station to see first-hand challenges experienced by residents about service delivery. Address: SAPS Station, 1 Hospital Street, Macassar, (next to Macassar Post-Office) ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON POLICE, MR FRANCOIS BEUKMAN For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)
